Implement the private `aggregate/2` helper for `MultiSeriesResampler`.

`aggregate(points, mode)` takes a non-empty list of `{timestamp_ms, value}` tuples that
all fall within the same bucket for a single series (already sorted ascending by
timestamp), and reduces them to one aggregated value according to `mode`:

- `:last` — the value of the point with the latest timestamp in the bucket.
- `:first` — the value of the point with the earliest timestamp in the bucket.
- `:count` — the number of points in the bucket, as an integer.
- `:sum` — the sum of the points' values.
- `:max` — the maximum of the points' values.
- `:min` — the minimum of the points' values.
- `:mean` — the arithmetic mean of the points' values, as a float.

Since the incoming `points` list is sorted ascending by timestamp, `:first` is the value
of the head and `:last` is the value of the tail. The function is only ever called with a
non-empty list (buckets with no points for a series are handled by the caller, which
substitutes `nil` / forward-fill instead of calling `aggregate/2`).

